So that's why we
want the small space.

00:12:10.204 --> 00:12:11.870
And that generates a
lot of interactions

00:12:11.870 --> 00:12:13.160
between the different people.

00:12:13.160 --> 00:12:16.007
But on the porch you actually
see the Mediterranean here

00:12:16.007 --> 00:12:18.340
and this is where the more,
the riskier projects happen.

00:12:18.340 --> 00:12:19.240
On this side.

00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:21.320
Like robots that run around.

00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:21.820
Right?

00:12:21.820 --> 00:12:23.540
So that's where
we have them now.

00:12:23.540 --> 00:12:29.850
And the whole thing starts by
people joining in Thursday.

00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:33.460
So it used to be Thursday
night, it now is Thursday noon.

00:12:33.460 --> 00:12:35.480
And they pitch their projects.

00:12:35.480 --> 00:12:37.810
So you say, hey, I want
to build this drawer

00:12:37.810 --> 00:12:39.580
and the drawer
will open and close

00:12:39.580 --> 00:12:41.160
if you push down towards it.

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:42.570
So you pitch.

00:12:42.570 --> 00:12:45.130
And many teams actually
dismantle that point and say,

00:12:45.130 --> 00:12:46.720
hey, your project
is so much cooler

00:12:46.720 --> 00:12:49.876
than mine so I'll just
move ahead and do that.

00:12:49.876 --> 00:12:51.750
That's Thursday,
that's what's going on.

00:12:51.750 --> 00:12:55.050
And by Saturday we're
actually doing demos.

00:12:55.050 --> 00:13:00.060
What happens in between
is things like that.

00:13:00.060 --> 00:13:02.700
This is a user generated dinner.

00:13:02.700 --> 00:13:06.750
What happens in the user
generated dinner by geeks?

00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:09.590
A flamethrower, 10
meter flamethrower,

00:13:09.590 --> 00:13:11.910
is used in order to
create creme brulee.

00:13:11.910 --> 00:13:12.940
So it's user generated.

00:13:12.940 --> 00:13:13.960
They do whatever.

00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:16.510
A quad copter goes
up above the barbecue

00:13:16.510 --> 00:13:18.480
in order to supply the
air supply because you

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:20.260
do want to have
a great barbecue.

00:13:20.260 --> 00:13:24.320
So last year was
biological cooking.

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:28.630
So anything that geeks do
then translates into food

00:13:28.630 --> 00:13:32.580
and it ends with trying to
convince our families that they

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:36.010
gave up on us for three
days for a good reason.

00:13:36.010 --> 00:13:39.900
So people from either the
sponsors or luminaries

00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:42.730
or people from industry
and definitely the families

00:13:42.730 --> 00:13:45.290
try and understand
what is that we do.

00:13:45.290 --> 00:13:47.870
And that ends Saturday 3:00 PM.

00:13:47.870 --> 00:13:52.130
So we start Thursday
2:00 PM to Saturday 3:00

00:13:52.130 --> 00:13:54.860
PM and all projects must be
completed within this time

00:13:54.860 --> 00:13:56.610
period.

00:13:56.610 --> 00:13:59.920
Some people cheat by doing
some preparation in advance,

00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:01.660
but everything is
done in three days.

00:14:01.660 --> 00:14:05.122
They are building by designers,
makers, hardware engineers,

00:14:05.122 --> 00:14:07.080
software engineers,
everything is built on site

00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:08.670
in order to create that.

00:14:08.670 --> 00:14:10.760
And the whole thing
has been running

00:14:10.760 --> 00:14:12.910
now-- it's the 10th year.

00:14:12.910 --> 00:14:15.540
And it's entirely
volunteer based event.

00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:20.810
So no one is paid in order
to do this weird thing.

00:14:20.810 --> 00:14:25.000
So this is the initial
team that started it.

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:28.440
And this year we actually
have 30 volunteers.

00:14:28.440 --> 00:14:30.350
So this year is
GeekCon X. We wanted

00:14:30.350 --> 00:14:34.320
to make it the biggest, baddest,
greatest projects of all

00:14:34.320 --> 00:14:36.420
the time and so we
have a very big team.

00:14:36.420 --> 00:14:38.870
And how you do-- oh, by numbers.

00:14:38.870 --> 00:14:40.470
I didn't remember
having this slide.

00:14:40.470 --> 00:14:41.900
So 180 people.

00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:43.900
This year is actually
going to be 200.

