We really like beer
so there's always

00:14:59.600 --> 00:15:01.480
a local brewery
that supplies us.

00:15:01.480 --> 00:15:05.160
But the interesting-- and we
have pretty much all the time

00:15:05.160 --> 00:15:05.810
coffee.

00:15:05.810 --> 00:15:08.620
But the interesting thing is
what's our goal in doing this.

00:15:08.620 --> 00:15:11.390
And the goal that we have
is 66% failure rates.

00:15:11.390 --> 00:15:15.560
So last year we failed because
we had a 50% success rate.

00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:18.480
And why do-- why do
you go for the 66%?

00:15:18.480 --> 00:15:22.330
The whole idea of GeekCon, much
like other venues like that,

00:15:22.330 --> 00:15:25.160
is building the infrastructure,
building the framework that

00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:27.120
makes people so
much more creative.

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:27.620
Right?

00:15:27.620 --> 00:15:29.430
And the way to make
them more creative

00:15:29.430 --> 00:15:32.820
is by telling them
we want you to fail.

00:15:32.820 --> 00:15:36.670
So there has been
projects like firing

00:15:36.670 --> 00:15:38.950
down mosquitoes with lasers.

00:15:38.950 --> 00:15:41.760
And that half worked because
they mostly hit people.

00:15:41.760 --> 00:15:44.720
But that-- so is that success,
is that failure, we don't know.

00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:46.340
But it's pretty cool.

00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:47.650
So we really want to fail.

00:15:47.650 --> 00:15:50.350
And some people think
that we're less crazy

00:15:50.350 --> 00:15:51.710
than we think that we are.

00:15:51.710 --> 00:15:53.931
So Google has been
helping us in many ways.

00:15:53.931 --> 00:15:55.430
But General Motors,
who would expect

00:15:55.430 --> 00:15:57.580
General Motors to
sponsor a bunch of geeks

00:15:57.580 --> 00:16:00.780
that try to useless stuff?

00:16:00.780 --> 00:16:03.990
Face.com, a company I founded,
was actually born there.

00:16:03.990 --> 00:16:06.940
So that's one great impact.

00:16:06.940 --> 00:16:08.730
So we got to know
each other, people

00:16:08.730 --> 00:16:10.550
get to know between teams.

00:16:10.550 --> 00:16:13.360
But that's a side effect.

00:16:13.360 --> 00:16:14.990
Interesting other
side effects is

00:16:14.990 --> 00:16:17.110
conferences that get
built because of that.

00:16:17.110 --> 00:16:19.700
And in my mind, that's
my goal for this session.

00:16:19.700 --> 00:16:22.930
So GeekCon, again,
insurance we can't

00:16:22.930 --> 00:16:26.112
bring people that
are younger than 18.

00:16:26.112 --> 00:16:28.070
So we are pressured by
some of the participants

00:16:28.070 --> 00:16:30.790
in order to create
GeekCon for kids.

00:16:30.790 --> 00:16:34.870
One day events and those kids
build the most crazy stuff.

00:16:34.870 --> 00:16:37.244
Much more-- they are much
less burdened with limitations

00:16:37.244 --> 00:16:37.910
than the parent.

00:16:37.910 --> 00:16:40.480
So the kid thinks of the
idea and you suddenly

00:16:40.480 --> 00:16:43.160
see everyone building into it.

00:16:43.160 --> 00:16:44.640
Which is awesome.

00:16:44.640 --> 00:16:45.670
TentTech, DrinkCon.

